Once we do that, we can then ask, okay, is this mostly driven by the

1228
01:10:42.112 --> 01:10:44.232
underlying genome doubling or the HR deficiency?

1229
01:10:44.292 --> 01:10:47.892
And we can see that by and large, there's these different classes of events

1230
01:10:47.952 --> 01:10:51.272
from arm level changes, whole chromosome changes, segmental aneuploidies are

1231
01:10:51.282 --> 01:10:52.702
driven by genome doubling.

1232
01:10:53.812 --> 01:10:57.352
And indeed, when we try to explain this by either the HR deficiency or the genome

1233
01:10:57.372 --> 01:11:00.362
doubling, we see that most of this variation is driven by the genome doubling

1234
01:11:00.452 --> 01:11:00.792
itself.

1235
01:11:03.272 --> 01:11:04.032
One

1236
01:11:05.472 --> 01:11:09.352
