1244
01:11:31.752 --> 01:11:35.522
both primary metastatic sites for cGAS, which is

1245
01:11:35.592 --> 01:11:39.392
a marker for double-stranded cytosolic

1246
01:11:39.412 --> 01:11:40.112
DNA,

1247
01:11:41.232 --> 01:11:44.892
which can be present when you often get one of these

1248
01:11:44.912 --> 01:11:48.692
desegregated chromosomes that through mitosis can end up becoming encapsulated

1249
01:11:48.852 --> 01:11:52.592
in these structures called micronuclei that often they tend to

1250
01:11:52.612 --> 01:11:56.512
have fairly weak nuclear envelopes, and when they rupture, they release the

1251
01:11:56.532 --> 01:11:58.012
double-stranded DNA into the cytosol.

1252
01:11:58.872 --> 01:12:02.692
So we developed a deep learning approach to detect these cGAS

1253
01:12:02.772 --> 01:12:06.482
positive punctate objects that you can see here in this

1254
01:12:06.512 --> 01:12:07.392
pseudocolor image,

1255
01:12:08.392 --> 01:12:12.272
that shows PanCK for epithelial cells, DAPI as a

1256
01:12:12.312 --> 01:12:15.752
marker for primary nuclei, and cGAS as a marker for ruptured micronuclei.

1257
01:12:16.312 --> 01:12:19.872
And so using this method, we can segment these micronuclei at scale and then

1258
01:12:19.912 --> 01:12:21.552
calculate rates of these processes.

1259
01:12:21.912 --> 01:12:24.152
And we see that indeed this is sort of a very common,

1260
01:12:25.432 --> 01:12:29.142
ongoing process that may have resulted in the past few cell divisions of

1261
01:12:29.172 --> 01:12:30.512
these cancer cells.

1262
01:12:31.792 --> 01:12:34.942
This is something that we then have tried to explore further in terms of the

1263
01:12:35.492 --> 01:12:36.692
impact that

1264
01:12:37.672 --> 01:12:41.212
the presence of these micronuclei and these missegregated chromosomes may be having

1265
01:12:41.252 --> 01:12:45.032
on cGAS DNA activation.And one fairly striking

1266
01:12:45.112 --> 01:12:48.352
finding that we saw is that rather than

1267
01:12:48.432 --> 01:12:52.272
